(15, 109, 'Cloud Backups with Ahsay', 'cloud-backups-with-asay', '<p><img src="images/ashay.png" alt="" width="278" height="161" /></p>\r\n<p>The World''s Leading Backup Software Vendor Ahsay™ Systems Corporation Limited is the world''s leading backup software vendor.</p>\r\n<p>Our top of the class backup software, Ahsay™ Backup Software, is trusted by 5,000,000 users worldwide. Currently, over 10,000 MSPs / VARs have partnered with us in delivering secure backup products and services to their business customers.</p>\r\n<h3>Background</h3>\r\n<p>To capture the increasing demand for convenient and reliable backup service to replace traditional backup methods, Ahsay Systems Corporation (previously named as Leb Shama) was established in 1999 with the vision of developing a world-class Internet-based online offsite remote backup solution. We aimed to provide a low-cost, automated and reliable backup solution to the business communities.</p>\r\n<p>The proposal of providing Ahsay™ Backup Service was first drafted in September of 2000. The service was launched four months later. This marked the first official release of the Ahsay™ Backup Software. With constant introduction of relevant backup features, the online backup service was becoming very successful. Eventually, service providers started licensing Ahsay™ ''s software to offer their own online remote backup services, and at the same, businesses began to use Ahsay™ Backup Software to fulfill their internal backup needs.</p>\r\n<h3>Mission</h3>\r\n<p>Our mission statement is: "Backing up businesses, not just data". To achieve this, apart from continuous product improvements and addition of features most relevant to the market, we strongly believe that paying attention to partners'' needs and market trends, offering professional and responsive support, as well as providing value-added expert services are also essential.</p>\r\n<p>The strength of Ahsay™ lies in our innovative ideas and superior technical expertise. These competitive edges will be further utilized to develop more business solutions which are cost-effective and revenue-generating to our partners. Looking ahead into the future, Ahsay™ is determined to offer more value-for-money online remote backup solutions to meet everyday needs. More business opportunities will be explored. More innovative products/services will be offered and finally more people and businesses will be benefited from using our software.</p>', '', 1, 12, '2014-10-01 03:49:00', 307, '', '2014-12-24 04:00:35', 307, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2014-12-23 03:49:41', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 8, 8, '', '', 1, 7, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(16, 110, 'Chrome security flaws', 'chrome-security-flaws', '<p><img src="images/google.png" alt="" width="316" height="213" /></p>\r\n<h3>Google Chrome tops list for security vulnerabilities... and it''s not a bad thing</h3>\r\n<p><br />A report from software vulnerability experts Secunia has revealed that security flaws in Google Chrome rose from 64 in August 2014 to 162 in October of the same year. Fellow web browser Avant was next highest-listed software product with 159, before the figures fell sharply with iTunes’ comparatively low number of 83 vulnerabilities. </p>\r\n<p>Chrome’s surprisingly high number of security flaws might not be a bad thing. According to Kasper Lindgaard, Secunia’s Director of Reasearch and Security, “it is almost always Google themselves who disclose the vulnerabilities”, and that Google’s top position in vulnerability rankings is “due to the vendor proactively hunting down and fixing vulnerabilities before anyone knows about them”.</p>\r\n<p>Lindgaard also stated that “Google run generous bounty programs” for those that discover security flaws. This encourages ‘white hat’ hackers to report them to the company for fixing rather than exploit them for personal gain. This, in combination with the fact that the search giant “invests a lot of internal resources” in finding and plugging these loopholes means that “Google run a fairly tight ship”.</p>\r\n<p>Google’s internal security may not be the whole story though. Lindgaard also noted that “Google Chrome is bundled with a number of third-party libraries” and that flaws in these - which are often less security-conscious than Google -  “may or may not make Google Chrome vulnerable too”.</p>\r\n<p>The report also offered a damning indictment of IBM, whose products “remain rife with vulnerabilities” courtesy of the third-party software they frequently come bundled with. The report urged “anyone running IBM products... to get busy patching their IBM applications”.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p>{jumi [*3] [Adam Shepherd] [http://www.pcauthority.com.au/News/398943,google-chrome-tops-list-for-security-vulnerabilities-and-its-not-a-bad-thing.aspx]}</p>\r\n<p><br /><br /></p>', '', 1, 12, '2014-12-09 04:12:00', 307, '', '2014-12-24 04:00:51', 307, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2014-12-23 04:12:16', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_layout":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 6, 7, '', '', 1, 20, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', '');
