(228, 16, 1, '', '2014-12-23 04:12:16', 307, 3656, '8b0438cb336dc72db5f7d7692aa6f1f8443387d9', '{"id":16,"asset_id":110,"title":"Chrome security flaws","alias":"chrome-security-flaws","introtext":"<p><img src=\\"images\\/google.png\\" alt=\\"\\" width=\\"316\\" height=\\"213\\" \\/><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>A report from software vulnerability experts Secunia has revealed that security flaws in Google Chrome rose from 64 in August 2014 to 162 in October of the same year. Fellow web browser Avant was next highest-listed software product with 159, before the figures fell sharply with iTunes\\u2019 comparatively low number of 83 vulnerabilities.\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Chrome\\u2019s surprisingly high number of security flaws might not be a bad thing. According to Kasper Lindgaard, Secunia\\u2019s Director of Reasearch and Security, \\u201cit is almost always Google themselves who disclose the vulnerabilities\\u201d, and that Google\\u2019s top position in vulnerability rankings is \\u201cdue to the vendor proactively hunting down and fixing vulnerabilities before anyone knows about them\\u201d.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Lindgaard also stated that \\u201cGoogle run generous bounty programs\\u201d for those that discover security flaws. This encourages \\u2018white hat\\u2019 hackers to report them to the company for fixing rather than exploit them for personal gain. This, in combination with the fact that the search giant \\u201cinvests a lot of internal resources\\u201d in finding and plugging these loopholes means that \\u201cGoogle run a fairly tight ship\\u201d.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Google\\u2019s internal security may not be the whole story though. Lindgaard also noted that \\u201cGoogle Chrome is bundled with a number of third-party libraries\\u201d and that flaws in these - which are often less security-conscious than Google - \\u00a0\\u201cmay or may not make Google Chrome vulnerable too\\u201d.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The report also offered a damning indictment of IBM, whose products \\u201cremain rife with vulnerabilities\\u201d courtesy of the third-party software they frequently come bundled with. The report urged \\u201canyone running IBM products... to get busy patching their IBM applications\\u201d.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><br \\/><br \\/><\\/p>","fulltext":"","state":1,"catid":"12","created":"2014-12-23 04:12:16","created_by":"307","created_by_alias":"","modified":"","modified_by":null,"checked_out":null,"checked_out_time":null,"publish_up":"2014-12-23 04:12:16","publish_down":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","images":"{\\"image_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"float_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_caption\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"float_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_caption\\":\\"\\"}","urls":"{\\"urla\\":false,\\"urlatext\\":\\"\\",\\"targeta\\":\\"\\",\\"urlb\\":false,\\"urlbtext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetb\\":\\"\\",\\"urlc\\":false,\\"urlctext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetc\\":\\"\\"}","attribs":"{\\"show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_titles\\":\\"\\",\\"show_tags\\":\\"\\",\\"show_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_position\\":\\"\\",\\"show_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_author\\":\\"\\",\\"link_author\\":\\"\\",\\"show_create_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_modify_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publish_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_item_navigation\\":\\"\\",\\"show_icons\\":\\"\\",\\"show_print_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_email_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_vote\\":\\"\\",\\"show_hits\\":\\"\\",\\"show_noauth\\":\\"\\",\\"urls_position\\":\\"\\",\\"alternative_readmore\\":\\"\\",\\"article_layout\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publishing_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_article_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_backend\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\":\\"\\"}","version":1,"ordering":null,"metakey":"","metadesc":"","access":"1","hits":null,"metadata":"{\\"robots\\":\\"\\",\\"author\\":\\"\\",\\"rights\\":\\"\\",\\"xreference\\":\\"\\"}","featured":"0","language":"*","xreference":""}', 0),
(229, 17, 1, '', '2014-12-23 04:49:16', 307, 4866, '6014c6fc1b22c400a94efb7042f5bbcd9c1068e1', '{"id":17,"asset_id":111,"title":"How to protect yourself online","alias":"how-to-protect-yourself-online","introtext":"<p><img src=\\"images\\/perzo-safelock-900-80-300x168.jpg\\" alt=\\"\\" \\/><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>There\\u2019s little question that hardware and software developers have become much better at delivering secure products.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Windows vulnerabilities are rarer, most software auto-patches these days and curated app stores can help users steer away from the shonkier sources of apps.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>But as the software has evolved, so have the net nasties. Mobiles, social networking, traffic direction systems and critical infrastructure have become common targets. Targeted breaches of online databases have been a large theme in the past year \\u2013 that\\u2019s not us getting hacked, but the people to whom we trust our data.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>And we have learnt that we have more than just criminals we have to worry about: governments and business have proven more than willing to snoop on our every online activity.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>So what can you do? We\\u2019ve put together a quick list of the major current threats and how to best avoid them.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Windows XP<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>On April 8, Microsoft called it quits on Windows XP and Office 2003. Even though both still enjoy a significant user base, there will be no more patches or updates for the operating system or office suite. That makes them uniquely vulnerable, and if you\\u2019re still using XP, it\\u2019s definitely time to think about upgrading.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\u00a0<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>Malware<\\/h3>\\r\\n<h4>The Problem<\\/h4>\\r\\n<p>For most users, malware remains the most pressing online threat. The term is short for malicious software, and it covers viruses, worms, trojans, spyware, ransomware and any other software that exists to ruin your day. A lot of people also use the terms to describe potentially unwanted software (PUP), which is the unwanted crud like browser toolbars and other adware that so often gets delivered with \\u201cfree\\u201d and sometimes with paid software.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Malware is nearly always installed by the user, typically by executing a script or opening an application that they shouldn\\u2019t have. Trojan horses account for some 70% of malware infections, and the traditional means of delivering malware is still around: downloads from dodgy sites and social engineering attacks (where the user is tricked into opening a file they shouldn\\u2019t) are prominent.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The effects of malware vary wildly, but the overwhelming trend in the last few years has been less \\u201cdestroy everything\\u201d and more \\u201clet\\u2019s steal or extort money from the user.\\u201d According to Sophos\\u2019 Security Threat Report 2014, we\\u2019ve seen a much greater emphasis on compromising financial records and information, on using infected computers for BitCoin mining, and on ransomware, where the documents on infected computers are encrypted with the promise of decryption only if the user pays a ransom.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>And then there are mobile viruses, which primarily affect Android because of its more open architecture. In the first quarter of 2014 alone, the number of mobile banking trojans almost doubled, with some high profile attacks like Faketoken targeting increasingly prominent mobile wallet systems.<\\/p>","fulltext":"","state":1,"catid":"12","created":"2014-12-23 04:49:16","created_by":"307","created_by_alias":"","modified":"","modified_by":null,"checked_out":null,"checked_out_time":null,"publish_up":"2014-12-23 04:49:16","publish_down":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","images":"{\\"image_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"float_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_caption\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"float_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_caption\\":\\"\\"}","urls":"{\\"urla\\":false,\\"urlatext\\":\\"\\",\\"targeta\\":\\"\\",\\"urlb\\":false,\\"urlbtext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetb\\":\\"\\",\\"urlc\\":false,\\"urlctext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetc\\":\\"\\"}","attribs":"{\\"show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_titles\\":\\"\\",\\"show_tags\\":\\"\\",\\"show_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_position\\":\\"\\",\\"show_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_author\\":\\"\\",\\"link_author\\":\\"\\",\\"show_create_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_modify_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publish_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_item_navigation\\":\\"\\",\\"show_icons\\":\\"\\",\\"show_print_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_email_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_vote\\":\\"\\",\\"show_hits\\":\\"\\",\\"show_noauth\\":\\"\\",\\"urls_position\\":\\"\\",\\"alternative_readmore\\":\\"\\",\\"article_layout\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publishing_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_article_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_backend\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\":\\"\\"}","version":1,"ordering":null,"metakey":"","metadesc":"","access":"1","hits":null,"metadata":"{\\"robots\\":\\"\\",\\"author\\":\\"\\",\\"rights\\":\\"\\",\\"xreference\\":\\"\\"}","featured":"0","language":"*","xreference":""}', 0),
